Was a totally
acceptable golf shot.

15:18.948 --> 15:20.315
- Acceptable?
- Mm-hmm.

15:20.316 --> 15:22.117
Yay.

15:22.118 --> 15:24.152
Do not be so hard on yourself.

15:24.153 --> 15:25.821
Did you take a look
at the standings this morning?

15:25.822 --> 15:27.789
We are in the hunt.
We are right in the hunt.

15:27.790 --> 15:30.792
No, no, you...
you're doing great.

15:30.793 --> 15:32.727
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

15:32.728 --> 15:34.329
Do you put the flower in it
or on the outside of it?

15:34.330 --> 15:35.397
Do you know?

15:35.398 --> 15:38.200
We just got to play it safe

15:38.201 --> 15:40.001
and avoid catastrophe.
Aah!

15:49.045 --> 15:50.912
Hey.
Hey, are you okay?

15:50.913 --> 15:53.181
Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

15:53.182 --> 15:55.317
I just...
a few cuts and scrapes.

15:55.318 --> 15:57.018
That was dramatic.

15:57.019 --> 15:59.788
Oh, Jack, you're bleeding.

15:59.789 --> 16:01.356
Yeah, on your head.
Come on.

16:05.042 --> 16:06.209
Minor laceration
at the hairline.

16:06.210 --> 16:07.544
Did you lose consciousness?
No.

16:07.545 --> 16:09.546
Only my pride was hurt.

16:09.547 --> 16:10.814
Okay. What's this?

16:10.815 --> 16:12.349
You don't know what that is?

16:12.350 --> 16:13.583
No, I do.
It's just...

16:13.584 --> 16:14.985
- a pen.
- Thank you.

16:14.986 --> 16:16.519
Spell "world" backwards.

16:16.520 --> 16:17.554
Why, you dyslexic?

16:17.555 --> 16:19.456
- No, I'm not.
- D-l-r-o-w.

16:19.457 --> 16:21.625
Mental status normal,
relatively speaking.

16:23.094 --> 16:24.461
All things considered,
not so bad.

16:24.462 --> 16:27.364
Yeah. Good thing
I landed next to the branch

16:27.365 --> 16:28.465
and not on it.

16:28.466 --> 16:30.900
So, uh, how'd this happen?

16:30.901 --> 16:34.437
They were coming right at us,
and I just lost control.

16:34.438 --> 16:35.839
Sweaty hands, I guess.

16:35.840 --> 16:37.540
I make you that nervous, huh?

16:37.541 --> 16:39.309
Okay. Would you walk
with me a sec?

16:39.310 --> 16:41.211
I just want to make sure
your balance is okay.

16:41.212 --> 16:42.379
Yeah.

16:42.380 --> 16:45.148
Thanks.
Um, so...

16:45.149 --> 16:47.684
I don't mean to pry,
but I think your hands have

16:47.685 --> 16:49.519
bigger problems than sweat.

16:49.520 --> 16:52.689
The, uh... the curvature of
your pinkie and ring fingers...

16:52.690 --> 16:54.224
I think you may have
a condition called...

16:54.225 --> 16:55.792
dupuytren's contracture...

16:55.793 --> 16:57.127
a progressive thickening
of the connective tissue

16:57.128 --> 16:59.329
in my hand.
Yeah. Exactly.

16:59.330 --> 17:01.298
I've been living with that
for about a year and a half.

17:01.299 --> 17:02.832
So have you looked
into radiotherapy,

17:02.833 --> 17:04.000
needle aponeurotomy?

17:04.001 --> 17:05.969
Or the series
of 12 surgeries I could have.

17:05.970 --> 17:08.471
Yes, I have.
And?

17:08.472 --> 17:10.839
Look, doc, I might be a golfer,

17:10.840 --> 17:13.009
but I don't make
Tiger Woods money...

17:13.010 --> 17:15.111
Or his caddie's money
or his caddie's caddie's money.

17:15.112 --> 17:17.213
Look, doc,
I'm a minor-leaguer.

17:17.214 --> 17:18.815
Yeah, minor or not,
you still need your hands

17:18.816 --> 17:20.317
to golf, right?
Yeah, I do.

17:20.318 --> 17:21.818
But I would be sidelined
way too long.

17:21.819 --> 17:23.353
I would lose the few sponsors
that I have.

17:23.354 --> 17:24.921
I might never be able
to come back.

17:24.922 --> 17:27.057
Or you'd come back stronger.
You don't know.

17:27.058 --> 17:28.892
I don't know,
and that's what scares me.

17:28.893 --> 17:30.260
I don't...

17:30.261 --> 17:32.329
I don't have anything else
to fall back on.

17:32.330 --> 17:34.597
So the way I see it,

17:34.598 --> 17:37.334
I just got to make the most
of the time I have left.

17:37.335 --> 17:39.502
Great. But one of these
could help extend that time.

17:39.503 --> 17:43.073
You know what people
started calling me

17:43.074 --> 17:44.941
after I blew the final hole
at the open?

17:44.942 --> 17:46.543
No.

17:46.544 --> 17:49.279
Captain hook.

17:51.849 --> 17:54.184
Ironic.

18:05.463 --> 18:08.998
Thank you so much.

18:08.999 --> 18:11.634
Okay, I leave
for London Thursday.

18:11.635 --> 18:12.802
I return Monday.

18:12.803 --> 18:14.003
I have juggled the schedule,

18:14.004 --> 18:15.405
so those should be
relatively light days.

18:15.406 --> 18:18.007
Divya, you're moving
to London in, like, a month.

18:18.008 --> 18:19.976
You really need to go there
next weekend too?

18:19.977 --> 18:22.379
Of course, divya.
It's fine. Come here.

18:22.380 --> 18:24.280
Take a look at this.

18:24.281 --> 18:25.849
Oh, for your golfes hand.

18:25.850 --> 18:27.550
Yeah, let's give them
a call, okay?

18:27.551 --> 18:30.120
Sure. I'm on it.

18:32.790 --> 18:36.059
Hank, I think I just located
dad's attorney.

18:36.060 --> 18:37.761
Wait, is this dad's phone?

18:37.762 --> 18:40.230
Yep. I stole it...Briefly,
just to find his lawyer.

18:40.231 --> 18:42.065
All right. Well, great.

18:45.136 --> 18:46.369
That's it?

18:46.370 --> 18:48.571
I got a work thing here, okay?

18:48.572 --> 18:50.840
Okay.

18:50.841 --> 18:53.276
Forgive me for thinking
our father,

18:53.277 --> 18:54.711
who just had a heart attack

18:54.712 --> 18:56.446
and is most likely headed
for federal prison,

18:56.447 --> 18:58.415
might interest you
more than a work thing.

18:58.416 --> 18:59.849
What do you want me to do, ev?

18:59.850 --> 19:01.184
Maybe care a little bit.

19:01.185 --> 19:02.952
I do care, okay?

19:02.953 --> 19:04.854
That's a funny way
of showing it.

19:04.855 --> 19:08.992
What do you want me
to do, obsess?

19:08.993 --> 19:11.494
I see what this is.

19:11.495 --> 19:12.962
This is you gloating.

19:12.963 --> 19:15.432
What? What are you...
what are you talking about?

19:15.433 --> 19:17.534
You've been suspicious
of dad since day one.

19:17.535 --> 19:18.868
I always said you were wrong.

19:18.869 --> 19:20.670
But you weren't wrong.
You were right.

19:20.671 --> 19:22.272
So now this is you
sitting there

19:22.273 --> 19:23.673
being all...

19:23.674 --> 19:24.741
Right.

19:24.742 --> 19:28.178
I am not gloating.
It's just...

19:28.179 --> 19:29.646
I don't need to know
the gory details

19:29.647 --> 19:33.183
of how wrong you were
or I was or he is.

19:33.184 --> 19:35.118
It won't fix anything,
and it'll only make me angry.

19:35.119 --> 19:38.388
And I am tired of being angry.

19:38.389 --> 19:40.223
See, this right here...
this thing...

19:40.224 --> 19:42.125
This might let me fix
a guy's hands.

19:42.126 --> 19:44.027
I like problems
I can fix, Evan.

19:44.028 --> 19:45.094
It's why I'm a doctor.

19:45.095 --> 19:46.663
Well, I'm not a doctor?

19:46.664 --> 19:48.264
I want the details...

19:48.265 --> 19:50.166
Just in case there are
any land mines out there

19:50.167 --> 19:52.135
we haven't stepped on
yet, okay?

19:55.072 --> 19:57.307
Fine.

19:57.308 --> 20:00.577
Just do yourself a favor
and try not to get hurt, okay?

20:00.578 --> 20:02.946
Thank you.

20:06.917 --> 20:08.284
Listen, you didn't hear it
from me,

20:08.285 --> 20:11.988
but, um, your family,
your father trusts you.

20:11.989 --> 20:13.256
And I'm gonna assume
that what I say

20:13.257 --> 20:15.492
stays between us, okay?
Absolutely.

20:15.493 --> 20:16.893
What you dug up is accurate.

20:16.894 --> 20:18.795
Your father got caught up in
a trading scheme in the spring.

20:18.796 --> 20:19.929
All right.
And he was convicted?

20:19.930 --> 20:21.264
Maybe he deserved it.

20:21.265 --> 20:22.799
Maybe he just got
the wrong judge

20:22.800 --> 20:24.267
in the wrong mood, you know?

20:24.268 --> 20:26.135
But, uh, yeah.

20:26.136 --> 20:28.104
And this happened
before the summer, right?

20:28.105 --> 20:29.772
Before he cleaned out
hankmed's bank account.

20:29.773 --> 20:32.342
Yeah. He was in a bad place
when he got out here.

20:32.343 --> 20:34.978
He didn't have any money,
didn't know where to turn.

20:34.979 --> 20:37.480
- Right.
- He was, uh...

20:37.481 --> 20:40.717
he was set to flee the state
in order to avoid sentencing.

20:40.718 --> 20:43.386
What?
He was going on the lam?

20:43.387 --> 20:44.687
Until he went to the Hamptons,

20:44.688 --> 20:47.257
at which point he opted
to work with the feds

20:47.258 --> 20:49.425
and try to make his sentence
go away.

20:49.426 --> 20:50.960
Why?
Because of us?

20:50.961 --> 20:53.530
He said he had a shot
at fixing things with his sons,

20:53.531 --> 20:55.532
that, uh...

20:55.533 --> 20:57.734
That you boys were
the most important thing to him.

20:57.735 --> 21:01.337
Whew.
Okay, um...

21:01.338 --> 21:03.640
So his sentencing hearing...

21:03.641 --> 21:06.476
He... he still has a chance
of probation, right?

21:06.477 --> 21:09.112
Or maybe community service
or something?

21:09.113 --> 21:11.748
I wouldn't count on it, son.

21:22.232 --> 21:25.134
Well, I see you picking
at your food, miss Casey,

21:25.135 --> 21:26.569
but I don't see you eating it.

21:26.570 --> 21:27.804
You're gonna need
your strength out there.

21:27.805 --> 21:29.405
Well, you know what?
I'm not hungry.

21:29.406 --> 21:30.773
I think I might be nervous.
Hey, guys.

21:30.774 --> 21:32.075
Hey, doc.
You want to join us?

21:32.076 --> 21:33.543
- Um...
- You know what?

21:33.544 --> 21:34.877
We have no time. We have to go
to the driving range.

21:34.878 --> 21:36.212
- Ah.
- We're only two strokes behind.

21:36.213 --> 21:38.047
We're in the hunt.

21:38.048 --> 21:39.782
- We take golf very seriously.
- Okay.

21:39.783 --> 21:41.317
And I like to win.

21:41.318 --> 21:44.120
But, Hank, I could really
use your help.

21:44.121 --> 21:46.556
If you like to win and you
need my help, you're in trouble.

21:46.557 --> 21:48.124
No, it's just I haven't played
golf in a while,

21:48.125 --> 21:49.626
and after two rounds
in two days,

21:49.627 --> 21:51.127
my back is really
stiffening up.

21:51.128 --> 21:52.528
How about you start
with two advil?

21:52.529 --> 21:53.630
- Deal.
- Okay.

21:53.631 --> 21:54.897
All right, eat quick.

21:54.898 --> 21:55.932
I'm gonna get the check,
all right?

21:55.933 --> 21:58.668
- Uh, real... you don't...
- No, I got it.

21:58.669 --> 22:01.270
Yeah, just let the girl pay.

22:01.271 --> 22:05.074
Competitive, beautiful,
buys me breakfast...

22:05.075 --> 22:06.409
I like this girl.

22:06.410 --> 22:09.145
- Uh-huh. So I did
some reading up on dupuytren's.

22:09.146 --> 22:10.480
Don't waste your time.

22:10.481 --> 22:12.749
And while the surgeries
you mentioned are one way to go,

22:12.750 --> 22:14.283
there's a brand-new drug
on the market.

22:14.284 --> 22:15.318
Waste your time.

22:15.319 --> 22:17.153
Your doctor might not know,

22:17.154 --> 22:18.855
'cause it was just approved
by the fda.

22:18.856 --> 22:20.890
I haven't seen a doctor
in a while.

22:20.891 --> 22:22.191
Okay, well,
it's an injection in your hand

22:22.192 --> 22:23.726
that basically melts
the lesions

22:23.727 --> 22:25.862
that cause the ligaments
in your fingers to tighten.

22:25.863 --> 22:27.563
No surgery?

22:27.564 --> 22:30.099
No surgery, but no guarantees.

22:30.100 --> 22:32.201
Nothing's guaranteed,
but that's great.

22:32.202 --> 22:33.803
Thanks, doc.
I'll... I'll check it out soon.

22:33.804 --> 22:36.239
How about now?

22:36.240 --> 22:38.741
It could take a few hours
to see results.

22:38.742 --> 22:40.810
Okay, this may pinch a little.

22:40.811 --> 22:43.513
Pinch away. I've tried
everything... nothing works.

22:43.514 --> 22:45.615
Life doesn't offer
too many mulligans.

22:45.616 --> 22:47.517
- Uh, mulligans?
- What kind of doctor are you?

22:47.518 --> 22:49.185
You too busy treating
the patients

22:49.186 --> 22:50.586
to learn your golf terms?

22:50.587 --> 22:53.589
Mulligan... fresh start,
do-over, second chance.

22:53.590 --> 22:56.693
I guess we could all use
a mulligan now and then.

22:58.529 --> 23:01.798
Okay...

23:01.799 --> 23:03.966
You are all set, my friend.

23:11.275 --> 23:12.675
- Whoo!
- Nice shot.

23:12.676 --> 23:13.910
Nice out, Casey.

23:13.911 --> 23:17.547
Oh, man.
I hit it fat.

23:17.548 --> 23:19.248
Oh, you knocked the back
out of it.

23:19.249 --> 23:20.483
That'll work.

23:20.484 --> 23:22.318
Hey, everything okay?
You called.

23:22.319 --> 23:26.589
I did.
Guys, I'll meet you down there.

23:26.590 --> 23:30.326
Hank, I need a shot
of cortisone a.S.A.P.

23:30.327 --> 23:32.128
And you know what?
Anything else

23:32.129 --> 23:33.262
you have in that bag of yours.

23:33.263 --> 23:35.832
My back is in spasm.
I can taste victory.

23:35.833 --> 23:37.366
Well, if everything hurts
that much,

23:37.367 --> 23:40.269
stop tasting and get some rest
and some ice.

23:40.270 --> 23:41.871
Are you suggesting I quit?

23:41.872 --> 23:43.639
I'm suggesting
you protect your body.

23:43.640 --> 23:45.408
You were thrown
from a golf cart yesterday.

23:45.409 --> 23:47.276
But, Hank, I'm nine holes away.

23:47.277 --> 23:48.778
Did you know it's bad form
to injure yourself

23:48.779 --> 23:50.780
at a charity tournament
benefiting a hospital?

23:50.781 --> 23:54.250
Hank, I want the win,
and I want that trophy.

23:54.251 --> 23:55.585
Okay.

23:55.586 --> 23:57.620
Not to mention...
I have a partner,

23:57.621 --> 23:59.222
and I don't want
to let him down.

23:59.223 --> 24:01.791
Yeah, I'm not finding
that argument very persuasive.

24:01.792 --> 24:02.959
You jealous?

24:02.960 --> 24:05.928
Yeah. That you prefer golf
to your health.

24:05.929 --> 24:07.530
No, I'm not jealous.
Sit down.

24:10.334 --> 24:11.901
How about we give you
a tens unit?

24:11.902 --> 24:13.770
Oh, you want to give me
electrical nerve stimulation?

24:13.771 --> 24:15.938
All right.
I want you to take it easy.

24:15.939 --> 24:18.341
<i>But since you're clearly gunning
for the cover of golf digest,</i>

24:18.342 --> 24:21.677
I'll settle
for just making you feel better.

24:21.678 --> 24:24.447
And in the future, sir,
anger management may help...

24:24.448 --> 24:26.582
both for you
and your five iron.

24:26.583 --> 24:28.584
Thank you.

24:33.891 --> 24:36.058
I'm sorry to just appear
like this,

24:36.059 --> 24:40.062
but I got worried when you
ignored the texts I sent you.

24:40.063 --> 24:42.398
Worried that I wasn't well?

24:42.399 --> 24:44.233
Worried that you
weren't returning my texts.

24:44.234 --> 24:46.202
Please, hear me out.
Adam...

24:46.203 --> 24:47.403
I'll... I'll talk fast.

24:49.473 --> 24:51.474
You're engaged,
and I knew that.

24:51.475 --> 24:53.409
And I never should have put you
in the position that I did.

24:53.410 --> 24:55.478
- Adam...
- Still talking.

24:55.479 --> 24:57.113
So I'm sorry for that.

24:57.114 --> 24:58.781
But I'm also...
I'm not sorry,

24:58.782 --> 25:01.117
because when we kissed,
I don't know...

25:01.118 --> 25:03.052
it just...
it felt good...

25:03.053 --> 25:05.288
And right.
Please don't.

25:05.289 --> 25:07.056
Look, if I'm wrong
and you didn't feel anything,

25:07.057 --> 25:08.691
tell me.

25:08.692 --> 25:11.260
And if you want me
to stop texting you...

25:11.261 --> 25:13.563
And stop showing up
at random golf tournaments...

25:13.564 --> 25:17.967
Just say so, and you'll never
see me again.

25:20.237 --> 25:22.839
When we kissed...

25:22.840 --> 25:26.509
I felt nothing except regret.

25:28.212 --> 25:29.679
I'm sorry.

25:44.294 --> 25:46.462
Cup right, all right.

25:46.463 --> 25:48.631
There's about a foot break.

25:48.632 --> 25:50.099
You got it?
Yeah.

25:50.100 --> 25:52.835
Okay. Piece of cake.

25:52.836 --> 25:54.036
Ms. Casey, you sink
this little putt,

25:54.037 --> 25:56.772
our team goes ahead
with one hole to play.

25:56.773 --> 25:58.774
Yeah, no pressure, huh?

25:58.775 --> 26:01.544
Hey, champions thrive
in the clutch.

26:01.545 --> 26:03.112
Or so they tell me.

26:27.187 --> 26:28.687
Her back's been bothering her.

26:28.688 --> 26:30.523
- And her stomach.
- One more time.

26:33.527 --> 26:35.761
You know what, guys?

26:35.762 --> 26:37.263
I am feeling much better.

26:37.264 --> 26:38.797
Yeah.

26:38.798 --> 26:41.300
Yeah, maybe just some more
of that electrical stimulation.

26:41.301 --> 26:43.502
It doesn't treat nausea.

26:43.503 --> 26:45.137
Well, it's probably
just a stomach bug.

26:45.138 --> 26:46.939
Really, guys, I'm... I'm fine.
Sit down.

26:46.940 --> 26:48.574
Jill, we're not
golfing anymore.

26:48.575 --> 26:50.409
Yeah, I ink this is
more than just a strained back.

26:50.410 --> 26:52.044
You may have suffered
a splenic tear

26:52.045 --> 26:53.379
when you hit the ground
after the accident.

26:53.380 --> 26:54.680
We need to take you
back to the tent

26:54.681 --> 26:56.115
and check
your hemoglobin levels.

26:56.116 --> 26:58.484
Well, doctor, my spleen's
been bothering me too.

26:58.485 --> 26:59.752
It has?

26:59.753 --> 27:01.453
Well, how can you tell?

27:01.454 --> 27:02.855
I was in the accident as well.

27:02.856 --> 27:04.823
Yeah, but, honey,
she hit the ground.

27:04.824 --> 27:06.892
We just went through
some leaves and webs.

27:06.893 --> 27:09.428
Your spleen is splendid.

27:09.429 --> 27:10.996
Um, Jill...

27:10.997 --> 27:13.732
Show me exactly where you
feel the pain on your back.

27:13.733 --> 27:15.201
It's just under
my shoulder blades.

27:15.202 --> 27:17.536
Well, you were right
about the bug,

27:17.537 --> 27:19.772
only it wasn't in your stomach.

27:19.773 --> 27:22.208
What is it?

27:23.443 --> 27:25.077
So this should help
with the pain.

27:25.078 --> 27:27.313
This'll counteract the toxin.

27:27.314 --> 27:30.249
I can't believe I didn't feel
a spider biting me.

27:30.250 --> 27:32.685
Well, you were thrown
out of a golf cart.

27:32.686 --> 27:34.954
Your mind
may have been elsewhere.

27:34.955 --> 27:36.989
A black widow bite isn't
so bad if you catch it early.

27:36.990 --> 27:39.992
You may feel groggy
or even a little loopy.

27:39.993 --> 27:42.661
Jack, I'm really sorry
about this.

27:42.662 --> 27:44.163
What are you apologizing for?

27:44.164 --> 27:46.332
Well, we were this close
to winning.

27:46.333 --> 27:48.100
You know what?
We'll get 'em next year, killer.

27:48.101 --> 27:50.436
Plus, now we don't have the
pressure of having to repeat.

27:50.437 --> 27:52.037
Repeat?

27:52.038 --> 27:53.072
Pardon?

27:53.073 --> 27:55.741
Repeat. Repeat.

27:55.742 --> 27:57.943
Repeat.

27:57.944 --> 28:00.679
Repeat.

28:00.680 --> 28:02.314
Hank, that's funny, right?

28:02.315 --> 28:03.782
Uh, yeah.

28:03.783 --> 28:05.484
"Uh, yeah."

28:05.485 --> 28:08.120
How cute are you
when your being all doctor-y?

28:08.121 --> 28:09.488
He's so cute.

