28:54.701 --> 28:56.635
- that's a good idea.
- Uh, yeah.

28:59.105 --> 29:00.606
Please stop licking my hand.

29:02.309 --> 29:04.310
Yeah, so that was a little...

29:04.311 --> 29:05.844
- Awkward.
- Yeah.

29:05.845 --> 29:07.413
Yeah. But, you know,
give her some time

29:07.414 --> 29:08.881
for the meds to wear off...
she'll be back.

29:08.882 --> 29:10.082
- Sure.
- Yeah.

29:10.083 --> 29:12.284
- Yeah.
- So how are your hands doing?

29:12.285 --> 29:14.253
- Good. Bad.
- Oh.

29:14.254 --> 29:15.821
Those injections
didn't do anything.

29:15.822 --> 29:17.790
Bummer...
I got to admit

29:17.791 --> 29:19.658
I was kind of getting
my hopes up a little bit.

29:19.659 --> 29:23.095
Here, let me try something
else... give me your hands.

29:23.096 --> 29:26.231
All right, this may hurt
a little, okay?

29:28.768 --> 29:30.703
Okay...

29:33.540 --> 29:35.641
Okay.
Agh, aha!

29:35.642 --> 29:36.875
Jeez, doc.

29:36.876 --> 29:39.845
I'm glad you have
a high pain threshold.

29:39.846 --> 29:42.414
Hol... hold on a second.

29:42.415 --> 29:44.750
I can move... I can move 'em.
Yeah.

29:44.751 --> 29:45.951
I can... I can move.

29:45.952 --> 29:47.553
Why didn't you just do
that before?

29:47.554 --> 29:49.254
The medication had to kick in
and loosen the ligaments.

29:49.255 --> 29:50.689
And we'll also do
a follow-up next week.

29:50.690 --> 29:53.225
This... this is amazing.

29:53.226 --> 29:54.793
Looks like you need
a new nickname.

29:54.794 --> 29:56.261
You got that right,
hanky panky.

29:56.262 --> 29:57.730
And so do I.

29:57.731 --> 30:00.632
Jack O'Malley...
Is back!

30:00.633 --> 30:02.201
That's great.

30:02.202 --> 30:04.169
Of course, now I guess
I have to deliver.

30:04.170 --> 30:06.004
Yeah, that's the thing
about second chances.

30:06.005 --> 30:08.040
If you get one, you...

30:08.041 --> 30:10.509
You kind of got to take it.

30:10.510 --> 30:12.511
I don't know how to thank you.

30:12.512 --> 30:14.179
Well, you could shake my hand.

30:17.650 --> 30:19.852
- Hit a hold-in-one,
win a boat.

30:19.853 --> 30:21.186
Everyone's welcome.

30:25.558 --> 30:27.993
Tough luck, buddy.

30:27.994 --> 30:29.695
Hey, what's up?

30:29.696 --> 30:31.363
Oh, my God,
what took you so long?

30:31.364 --> 30:33.932
I texted you 100 times.
We need to talk.

30:33.933 --> 30:36.068
- Okay, then why are you playing
in a hole-in-one contest?

30:36.069 --> 30:38.003
'Cause I support our troops.

30:38.004 --> 30:39.605
You know she's
not a real sailor, right?

30:40.707 --> 30:44.009
So I got some serious
4-1-1 on dad.

30:44.010 --> 30:46.879
You were right about him,
but so was I.

30:46.880 --> 30:49.248
Wait, that was what
you texted me 100 times about?

30:49.249 --> 30:50.649
- No, I...
- It's your turn.

30:50.650 --> 30:52.284
Oh, really?
Okay, cool.

30:52.285 --> 30:54.153
Um, we'll talk more in private.

30:54.154 --> 30:55.187
It's a private thing anyway.

30:55.188 --> 30:56.822
After I swing. Great.
Okay.

30:58.658 --> 31:00.626
Okay.

31:00.627 --> 31:02.928
Thanks.
You're welcome.

31:02.929 --> 31:05.531
All right, ev, let's do this.

31:05.532 --> 31:06.965
You got this.

31:09.202 --> 31:10.602
Noonan!

31:10.603 --> 31:12.871
Sorry.

31:12.872 --> 31:14.573
You can do it.

31:14.574 --> 31:15.641
All in the wrist...

31:15.642 --> 31:17.776
And the hips.

31:17.777 --> 31:19.945
Wrist, hips.

31:32.525 --> 31:34.960
It's in the hole!
It's in the hole!

31:34.961 --> 31:36.395
It's a hole in one!

31:37.797 --> 31:39.031
That was awesome!

31:39.032 --> 31:40.966
Dude! You...

31:40.967 --> 31:42.568
hello?
You just won the boat.

31:42.569 --> 31:44.336
You won it!
Here. Will you sign for me?

31:44.337 --> 31:45.671
I got to go.
I got to go.

31:45.672 --> 31:47.306
What...?

31:53.746 --> 31:56.181
So should...

32:18.071 --> 32:20.105
So I just want to begin

32:20.106 --> 32:22.341
by apologizing on behalf
of the Lawson family

32:22.342 --> 32:24.009
for what my father did.

32:24.010 --> 32:27.112
You needn't apologize.

32:27.113 --> 32:29.014
Come.

32:29.015 --> 32:30.549
This is...

32:38.091 --> 32:41.960
Do you know why I gave you
that file, Mr. Lawson?

32:48.368 --> 32:49.835
No.

32:49.836 --> 32:53.505
Well, Hank seems
to understand your father.

32:53.506 --> 32:55.874
I thought it might be time
that you did as well.

32:58.411 --> 33:00.145
All right.

33:00.146 --> 33:01.914
Why are you being so nice to us

33:01.915 --> 33:04.650
after what our father
did to you?

33:04.651 --> 33:07.719
Well, we are
not our parents, are we?

33:07.720 --> 33:09.955
We cannot be held responsible
for their actions.

33:09.956 --> 33:11.890
Don't you agree?

33:11.891 --> 33:15.360
Good.

33:15.361 --> 33:16.495
Evan...

33:16.496 --> 33:18.597
If you desire for your father

33:18.598 --> 33:21.533
to have a less stressful
environment

33:21.534 --> 33:23.001
in which to recuperate...

33:23.002 --> 33:24.770
Less stressful?

33:24.771 --> 33:26.038
There are climates
more comfortable

33:26.039 --> 33:28.340
where Eddie r. Lawson
might convalesce.

33:29.976 --> 33:34.446
And I can make
those arrangements.

33:37.684 --> 33:40.619
Well, you think about it.

33:47.293 --> 33:48.994
So he just knocks
the white off the ball.

33:48.995 --> 33:52.197
It goes sailing,
bounces off the golf cart,

33:52.198 --> 33:54.099
and then, bam,
right into the hole!

33:54.100 --> 33:57.869
I mean, how Evan is that?

33:57.870 --> 34:00.205
It's so Evan!

34:00.206 --> 34:02.507
And now we have to watch him
christen the boat,

34:02.508 --> 34:05.611
you know, pretend
he's Captain ahab,

34:05.612 --> 34:08.013
even though he's more like
Captain crunch.

34:08.014 --> 34:11.750
I guess the upside is he could
go off on a three-hour tour.

34:11.751 --> 34:13.118
Nothing on that?

34:13.119 --> 34:15.020
♪ A three-hour tour ♪

34:15.021 --> 34:17.723
Hello?
Hank...

34:19.359 --> 34:21.326
I crossed an unacceptable line.

34:22.695 --> 34:24.795
I became involved
with a patient.

34:24.797 --> 34:26.598
You did?

34:28.534 --> 34:30.435
I kissed him.

34:32.105 --> 34:33.572
But I ended it.

34:33.572 --> 34:35.741
And I will, of course,

34:35.742 --> 34:38.810
in no way continue
to treat him medically.

34:38.811 --> 34:41.580
That's why you're
flying out to London tonight...

34:41.581 --> 34:42.848
To see raj.

34:42.849 --> 34:46.818
I can only imagine
how furious you are with me.

34:46.819 --> 34:50.121
It was highly unprofessional.

34:50.123 --> 34:52.190
And if you need me to,

34:52.190 --> 34:55.460
I will resign from hankmed,
effective immediately.

34:55.460 --> 34:57.329
Resign?

34:57.330 --> 34:58.764
Please. I... no.

34:58.765 --> 35:00.732
I don't care about that.

35:00.733 --> 35:03.535
What I care about is you.

35:03.536 --> 35:05.337
Are you okay?

35:07.707 --> 35:09.007
No.

35:12.378 --> 35:14.179
No.

35:14.180 --> 35:15.480
I'm not.

35:17.784 --> 35:21.486
But I've got it under control.

35:21.487 --> 35:23.655
Is there anything I can do?

35:26.192 --> 35:28.593
No.

35:28.594 --> 35:30.195
No, but, uh...

35:32.098 --> 35:35.801
Oh, but thank you so much
for being you.

35:41.908 --> 35:43.842
I'm sorry.

35:51.993 --> 35:54.394
My point is that
everything dad did,

35:54.395 --> 35:55.562
he did to be with us.

35:55.563 --> 35:56.997
Yeah, and my point is
that you learned that

35:56.998 --> 35:58.431
from his criminal
defense attorney.

35:58.432 --> 36:01.668
You see, this is why people
like me better than you, Hank.

36:01.669 --> 36:02.836
You're a gray cloud.

36:02.837 --> 36:04.337
I'm a silver lining, myself.

36:04.338 --> 36:06.473
Wait. People like you
better than me?

36:06.474 --> 36:07.841
They will, when they find out

36:07.842 --> 36:09.776
♪ about my new yacht ♪

36:09.777 --> 36:12.479
- Oh, God.
- I'm a yacht owner.

36:12.480 --> 36:15.215
I own a yacht, a giant yacht.

36:15.216 --> 36:16.917
What do you think
about the name

36:16.918 --> 36:19.052
<i>fairway to Evan.</i>

36:19.053 --> 36:21.321
Hmm. You spend a lot
of time on that one?

36:21.322 --> 36:22.823
Like two hours.

36:22.824 --> 36:25.258
It's a good use of your time.

36:25.259 --> 36:27.194
<i>And, Evan, it's a boat.</i>

36:27.195 --> 36:29.663
Just for that, I now have an
extra spot at the christening.

36:29.664 --> 36:31.565
No, plea...
please let me come!

36:31.566 --> 36:33.567
- Nope.
- Hey, Hank.

36:33.568 --> 36:34.835
Hey.

36:34.836 --> 36:36.069
Captain stubing.

36:38.606 --> 36:41.408
Make that two extra spots.

36:41.409 --> 36:44.244
- This is for you.
- Really?

36:44.245 --> 36:45.979
Thank you, Jill.

36:53.654 --> 36:55.755
Um, knickers.

36:55.756 --> 36:56.923
Yeah.

36:56.924 --> 36:58.558
They're a consolation prize.

36:58.559 --> 36:59.759
Why do I need to be consoled?

36:59.760 --> 37:01.394
I'm about to pick up
my brand-new yacht.

37:01.395 --> 37:02.729
Yeah...

37:02.730 --> 37:04.397
About that...

37:04.398 --> 37:06.733
Oh, I don't know where this
is going, but I like it.

37:06.734 --> 37:08.368
All right, what?

37:08.369 --> 37:10.270
Uh, while I was still
loopy from the meds,

37:10.271 --> 37:14.274
I may have let it slip
that you worked for hankmed.

37:14.275 --> 37:15.642
So?

37:15.643 --> 37:17.510
So tournament employees

37:17.511 --> 37:19.479
aren't eligible for prizes.

37:19.480 --> 37:21.014
As well they shouldn't be.

37:34.061 --> 37:35.528
Well...

37:35.529 --> 37:38.932
I'm, a... I'm a yachtsman
without a yacht.

37:40.368 --> 37:42.969
I look freakin' ridiculous now.

37:42.970 --> 37:44.104
Yeah.

37:44.105 --> 37:45.639
That's why you look ridiculous.

37:45.640 --> 37:47.240
Be nice.

37:47.241 --> 37:49.309
- I'm gonna go change.
- Okay.

37:49.310 --> 37:52.245
Don't forget your knickers.

37:52.246 --> 37:53.647
Evan, I'm sorry.

37:55.416 --> 37:57.484
So...

37:57.485 --> 37:58.885
You're taking up golf?

37:58.886 --> 38:00.887
Yeah.

38:03.691 --> 38:04.991
Bam!
It's not so hard.

38:04.992 --> 38:06.326
I don't see
what the big deal is.

38:06.327 --> 38:07.327
You want to play?
I'll take you down.

38:07.328 --> 38:08.929
Really?

38:08.930 --> 38:11.031
Nah, I can't. I just wanted
to give Evan his knickers.

38:11.032 --> 38:12.732
And thank you for that.

38:12.733 --> 38:15.335
Yeah, and to apologize

38:15.336 --> 38:17.804
for anything I may have said
while loopy.

38:17.805 --> 38:19.139
Oh, yeah, no...

38:19.140 --> 38:20.640
no idea
what you're talking about.

38:20.641 --> 38:22.776
So I didn't say
anything stupid?

38:22.777 --> 38:24.177
I'm afraid I can't say.

38:24.178 --> 38:25.612
Doctor-patient
confidentiality.

38:25.613 --> 38:27.814
Oh, come on, Hank,
I'm the patient.

38:27.815 --> 38:30.417
No, that was a Jill
I have never seen before.

38:30.418 --> 38:33.820
You sure you don't want to putt?
I can't. Jack's waiting.

38:33.821 --> 38:35.622
Jack? Jack.

38:35.623 --> 38:37.624
Right. Okay.

38:37.625 --> 38:39.025
Yeah, no, that's cool.

38:39.026 --> 38:40.527
Yeah.

38:40.528 --> 38:42.729
So, you know,
whether you heard or not

38:42.730 --> 38:45.265
or whether I said it or not,

38:45.266 --> 38:48.335
I'm sorry for anything
too stupid I may have let slip.

38:50.404 --> 38:54.541
What if I may have
kind of liked it?

38:55.876 --> 38:57.077
You may have?

38:57.078 --> 38:58.611
Yeah, I may have.

38:58.612 --> 39:00.547
I don't know... with everything
that happened with my father,

39:00.548 --> 39:02.816
I guess it's made me
reassess things.

39:02.817 --> 39:06.286
- What kind of things?
- All kinds of things.

39:06.287 --> 39:09.089
But let's not do this now.
Jack's waiting.

39:09.090 --> 39:10.357
Yeah.

39:10.358 --> 39:11.891
Yeah.

39:11.892 --> 39:15.195
- Another time?
- Yeah, some other time.

39:22.970 --> 39:25.138
I miss you too.

39:38.786 --> 39:41.888
Who doesn't love the beach?

39:41.889 --> 39:42.956
It's calming.

39:42.957 --> 39:44.524
That's good for you.
Yeah.

39:44.525 --> 39:47.894
Yeah, but the Hamptons
can be stressful, right?

39:47.895 --> 39:49.662
Which isn't good for you.

39:49.663 --> 39:53.333
Dad, do you ever think maybe
there's someplace else

39:53.334 --> 39:54.901
where you might be
more comfortable?

39:54.902 --> 39:56.436
Yeah, no, 'cause, I mean,
this is so grueling.

39:56.437 --> 39:57.504
Wow.

39:57.505 --> 39:58.872
Why would you want
to stay here?

39:58.873 --> 40:01.141
Well, there are climates
more comfortable

40:01.142 --> 40:03.676
where dad could...
you know, could convalesce.

40:03.677 --> 40:05.945
Why are you speaking like that?

40:05.946 --> 40:08.281
- Uh...
- I got my two boys...

40:08.282 --> 40:10.850
Miss Newberg.

40:10.851 --> 40:13.353
Look at this view.

40:13.354 --> 40:14.721
Does it get
any better than this?

40:14.722 --> 40:15.889
Come on.

40:15.890 --> 40:18.258
Schmoopy!

40:18.259 --> 40:20.527
Oh, m...
would you look at her?

40:20.528 --> 40:22.228
Is that a dream?

40:22.229 --> 40:24.964
Oh, you know what?
Somebody should go and help her.

40:24.965 --> 40:27.000
And my heart, I would, but...

40:27.001 --> 40:28.201
oh, I got it.

40:28.202 --> 40:29.469
No, no, I got to get
another beer anyway.

40:29.470 --> 40:31.171
Thank you, Evan.

40:31.172 --> 40:33.506
Thanks, Evan.

40:33.507 --> 40:35.275
I have a confession to make.

40:35.276 --> 40:37.010
Oh, God.

40:37.011 --> 40:38.812
Here we go.
What?

40:38.813 --> 40:40.814
I can't swim.

40:40.815 --> 40:43.716
There, I said it.
Okay.

40:43.717 --> 40:45.151
Eddie r. Lawson cannot swim.

40:45.152 --> 40:47.287
I can't even dog-paddle
to safety.

40:47.288 --> 40:48.421
What are you talk...
we used to swim

40:48.422 --> 40:49.789
all the time
when we were little.

40:49.790 --> 40:51.124
I remember, we...
No, you remember

40:51.125 --> 40:53.059
me saying I could swim,

40:53.060 --> 40:55.061
me bragging
about how much of a...

40:55.062 --> 40:56.496
like a fish I was.

40:56.497 --> 40:57.697
That was just all talk.

40:57.698 --> 40:59.299
All right, okay.
So you can't swim.

40:59.300 --> 41:01.734
You're telling me this why?

41:01.735 --> 41:03.703
Because when I told you
I could swim,

41:03.704 --> 41:06.239
that was the first lie
I ever told you.

41:07.808 --> 41:09.509
Okay. So...

41:09.510 --> 41:11.678
but why lie
about that? I...

41:11.679 --> 41:13.413
Because I didn't want
to be the guy

41:13.414 --> 41:16.149
who couldn't do everything.

41:16.150 --> 41:19.185
I wanted to be your hero.

41:19.186 --> 41:21.221
We didn't need you
to be our hero.

41:21.222 --> 41:23.790
I needed it.

41:26.026 --> 41:29.028
You know how some people
have, like, um...

41:29.029 --> 41:31.698
A near-death experience,
and it just changes their life?

41:31.699 --> 41:33.233
That happen to you?

41:33.234 --> 41:36.302
No, I'm too old
to have anything change me.

41:36.303 --> 41:38.338
But I swear to you,

41:38.339 --> 41:42.041
there was a moment
when I saw you and Evan

41:42.042 --> 41:43.843
as little boys.

41:43.844 --> 41:48.581
Yeah, when you had your heart
attack, there was a moment...

41:48.582 --> 41:50.383
I thought
we were gonna lose you.

41:50.384 --> 41:52.485
- Really?
- Yeah.

41:52.486 --> 41:54.487
And I realized
I don't want to lose you.

41:54.488 --> 41:56.789
I couldn't.
I can't.

41:58.659 --> 42:01.661
I guess what
I'm trying to say is, uh...

42:01.662 --> 42:05.064
I want you to stick around
to be our dad.

42:07.067 --> 42:09.302
You're giving me
a second chance.

42:09.303 --> 42:12.238
Call it a mulligan.

